title: Grades 6-8
subject: Career Development Framework For College and Career Readiness (2022-)

document.title: Maryland Career Development Framework For College and Career Readiness Grades Pre-K – Postsecondary (PS)/Adult

8F16EEA6CE6944C7878E10039489FE40.description: Evaluate the impact of lifelong learning on one’s ability to function effectively in a diverse and changing economy.

4C4B82F0491943838D0C044C36B60617.description:
Explain how education, work,
family, national crisis and
economic conditions affect
decisions.

410C0E9AB9D84B48B8E7837156F98110.description: Apply career management and decision-making skills to update ones’ career plan as needed.

6DA235E378E64354B81F1EA6DFC46A00.description:
Career Satisfaction and Transition – Individuals shall demonstrate how the ongoing attainment of knowledge and skills enhances one’s ability to function and transition
effectively in a diverse and changing economy.

37B8F1BB47204CB3B1FD18E3D7F970D6.description: Understand how academic, technical, cross cluster and employability skills are needed to obtain or create, maintain, and advance in one’s career.

225132283ADC4265B12C2791A49EEA01.description: Job-Seeking and Advancement – Students shall demonstrate skills to secure, maintain and advance in employment.

3D871D4F8FC74E5687D095BEBFB377CE.description: Use the selected decision-making process/model to update and modify the six-year academic and career plan.

455987D1CB884EF6BB6D0C09EC9FB121.description:
Explore academic and careerrelated skills and the Skills for
Success through project-based
learning and career connecting
activities.

9579E7C4474544B5893D0222BFE5F907.description:
Apply cluster content knowledge
and skills (foundation, pathway,
cross cluster) through
technology, research, problemsolving, and project-based
learning.

898CF1E90ADB406DA5409A2382CAB0EF.description:
Apply academic content
standards of the Maryland State
Curriculum.

30DDB0B3163A41E69B485062DEE3AC2A.description: Acquire cluster and academic content knowledge and skills to succeed in high school and beyond.

78826595464D4E7695BAAF94588E2A29.description:
Career Preparation: Students shall prepare for postsecondary and career success through a sequenced academic and technical program of study and related workplace
experiences.

30F94EDCABB047CCBE15E5A93A14874C.description:
Identify how cultural beliefs and
attitudes impact one’s career
decisions.

2EF5077A629C4A3890D44D947F1DF951.description:
Explain/apply steps of a
decision-making model to inform
academic and career planning.

8D8C5BF7AB6847D0AEE7F40B5EA4526D.description: Use a process/model for knowing and thinking about how one makes decisions.

1267F945CE374C9E90CCC6BD780449C6.description:
Select options for further
education and/or training (i.e.
dual enrollment, articulated
credit, advanced placement,
certification, two-year colleges,
four-year colleges,
apprenticeships, and technical
schools).

4AC1DD328DB046ED90D9B014B1A98F4C.description:
Explore specific learning
experiences within and across
career clusters.

54320AF96BF243AF988A503AB7CCE795.description:
Investigate program sequences
for career clusters including CTE
programs of study of interest that
overlap with other career
pathways.

0B09C2BD15A24662A0B14316F8585EA5.description:
Explore the requirements for
effective transition from one
learning level to the next (i.e.
middle to high school and high
school to postsecondary).

1697ADFCC3F942BA8C54996E1F760633.description:
Develop an academic and career
plan that includes postsecondary
options.

00B14DE634A645BBA9C32BCA0794C3C0.description:
Prepare an academic and career plan based on high school graduation requirements, a sequence of Career Technology Education (CTE) program of study courses,
related academics and postsecondary options.

010D59A3EBC14E04B2C0A4099B99AFC5.description:
Career Exploration – Students shall assess career cluster choices and related career pathways including Career Technology Education (CTE) programs of study in order to
develop an academic and career plan.

8CA83A18708945379DD49CF4BBA9D86D.description:
Explore that one has personal,
leisure, community, work roles,
and responsibilities which must
be balanced and that there are
many ways to do so.

19C13289529D4D9CA2A3FC2C6F6F2B6B.description: Understand that balancing personal, leisure, community, learner and work roles is an important part of one’s career development.

03BC32A40B8341D0879462B581C6BCC5.description:
Explain how decision-making
may involve compromise and
cite examples.

123F8820ECB6406794502A7A388CA03A.description:
Negotiate alternatives and their
outcomes to make informed
decisions.

6EBCA984929645999B842AA6D694E2CD.description:
Recognize how one’s personal
priorities (e.g. financial,
educational, leisure) are part of
one’s decision-making.

F35676EB9E9B48769007DCFBCD0385D7.description:
Examine the relationships
among education, skills, career
choices, economic conditions
and income.

65A5789EEEDA4EFF864437788C09D492.description:
Identify resources for gathering
career information relevant to
making a decision.

653B4143D3AB4DD2AD95ED75A3BE5CC0.description: Recognize that decision-making is an important part of an individual’s career development.

19D893A8A7BB4B73BA5DB7B6CA1A1023.description:
Evaluate assessments of personal
career results to knowledge of
self and career clusters.

AAD250DF4B824571A2811F2CA4B0E6A0.description:
Investigate career clusters and
career options, including those
that may be nontraditional (i.e.
relative to one’s gender, race,
culture, or ability.)

3D2504C90AED43BDACC48E4A178C762F.description:
Recognize that there are a
variety of resources available
which vary in quality such as
accuracy, bias, timeliness and
impartiality.

A9A696C4A74B4F3FAFA88D7180911F90.description:
Recognize the relevance of
career information to career
planning including, knowledge
about career clusters and related
economic information, career
options, education degrees, and
training requirements.

1C20DB19D6184FD3BEA06C71AA17555B.description: Understand how accurate, current and unbiased career information is necessary for successful career planning and management using career clusters.

EAECA5CA640A43A19349BDEB62AAB9EA.description:
Use technology to access, store,
manage, analyze, and
communicate information to
enhance and improve
achievement.

92873530697849D092B30609E769A465.description:
Use study skills, strategies and
learning habits to improve
achievement.

8476208247634C6CA5D39FC431D9C809.description:
Assess one’s educational
achievement and explain how it
impacts on the selection and
attainment of career options to
develop personal and career
goals.

739EEBBFBD1348C2B34B645BD0B9A02F.description:
Identify the connections between
one’s educational achievement
and personal and career goals.

A4E9D7D607664C398B24EFD5ABF9B401.description:
Use knowledge of one’s learning
style, positive attitude, and
behaviors to improve educational
attainment and adjust behavior,
when needed, to maximize
achievement.

A6BA282C41D940CFB87A42F20B06468A.description: Understand the connections among educational achievement, lifelong learning and the career options across career pathways.

D5B630E2A19746A88474CEA40FDF4917.description:
Compare/contrast the shift in the
work organization of the 21st
century versus the past.

F716DBB4675D49AF8709B913CCC74206.description:
Research occupations and
careers within each career cluster
and identify academic and CTE
programs of study to inform
academic and career planning

4855EF807B4E4FED8FF7C45C713D9A0A.description:
Describe how career clusters
relate to the needs and functions
of Maryland’s economy.

9BE1407EE8004957B13CE088EE9176B1.description:
Identify career clusters and
related CTE programs of study.

0695106C6F0E4A7592EADD840194BC3E.description: Analyze/compare the industries represented in Maryland’s 10 Career Clusters and how they relate to the needs and functions of the economy and society.

B1148E859F8E418B87C1CC9A6F50B030.description:
Career Awareness – Students shall use the Maryland Career Clusters and career pathways including Career and Technology Education (CTE) programs of study in order to
understand their relationship to educational achievement and life-long learning.

4E941B8BDE2D4424BF854565ABCAD402.description:
Analyze financial choices based
on available resources, needs,
and wants for goods and
services.

77144DAFCA68441390D4F20E9C55E51A.description:
Assess career and academic
interests to make decisions about
academic course selection and
career program of study choices.

4FCB7283EFA94FAEAF718102C4EB925E.description:
Demonstrate an awareness of
strategic thinking to make
effective decisions about goals
for learning and performance.

DFB36ED058FB40F29F51EB3F8E6FE847.description: Apply self-knowledge to decision-making and goal-setting.

A7BF0C5F73ED48B8A3C621719D8957A2.description:
Recognize that one’s motivations
and aspirations are likely to
change with time and
circumstances.

CAFDBFDA273D42C4B3675CC51692295B.description:
Demonstrate adaptability and
flexibility when initiating or
responding to change.

150AA672BE624E51ABC8170F007F2488.description:
Recognize that external events
often cause life changes.

92379CA12A41481D8D8BC04A288DE93F.description:
Identify situations and access
resources, including other
people, to seek assistance when
needed.

7BB7D26F4C724566A2C3B7C764FEE2A8.description:
Recognize that growth and
change in mind and body is
experienced throughout life.

1FD9E6C19862415B8C478AD0A3B5102E.description: Recognize that growth and change are integral parts of the career development process.

02B4851C43374B2DADAE8B26C71A1DF2.description:
Demonstrate, problem-solve and
evaluate communication
experiences and use of effective
strategies such as paraphrasing,
reflections, active listening, and
assertive communication.

3F361C3207744676A6BECA34227BC85E.description:
Identify and resolve conflicts and
bring to consensus when
appropriate.

E31D62A77B784E80865FE8A29519F455.description:
Analyze the impact of academic
achievement on the ability to
work cooperatively in a group.

5F20FD31C877465D97014772BD4FD973.description:
Demonstrate personal
responsibility for actions
including dealing with outside
pressures and contributing to
group activities.

E83BBA1251CB4F82895969E6498D9ECD.description:
Assess the degree to which
interactions and feedback is used
to adjust behavior in group
activities in a way that is honest,
fair, helpful, and respectful.

7FA68C0328AE4E2288CCC195994C442F.description: Demonstrate positive interpersonal skills and respect for diversity to facilitate one’s career development.

7644AFA0FB58473B9CDAF64C34284735.description:
Engage in behaviors and express
attitudes that positively affect
self-concept and the self-concept
of others.

4C94A803D2034C23AF53FAE18064510A.description:
Demonstrate and evaluate
behaviors that show selfconfidence, self-efficacy, and a
positive self-concept.

1E10257B74E54345B5EB372F5A4A7CFB.description:
Identify abilities, strengths, skills
and talents as seen by self and
others and explain the
significance to education and
career plans.

EAA1E6B6C5BF4389B093690929C0F951.description:
Demonstrate behavior and
decisions that reflect interests,
likes and dislikes.

DD35B0E7264F4E95B05A8995EDA3EBA2.description: Acquire and apply self-knowledge to understand one’s abilities, strengths, interests, skills, and talents as seen by self and others.

B1C0EA73ADEB42308241200F0BA9BA7A.description: Self-Awareness – Students shall acquire and apply self-knowledge in order to develop personal, learning and career goals.
